article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 80, Louisiana Lafayette 42
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Matt Kingsley scored 16 points and Antuane Miller had 13 to help Stephen F. Austin beat Louisiana-Lafayette 80-42 on Saturday night. Josh Alexander added 10 points for Stephen F. Austin (5-4), which shot 75 percent from the field in the second half and 65 percent for the game. Ross Mouton scored 15 and David Dees had 14 for Louisiana Lafayette (2-6). The Ragin' Cajuns shot just 32 percent from the field and made just three of 14 3-point attempts.
